  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "In order to get more efficient compilation on Besu, we should add support for GraalVM AOT. \n\nWhen doing so, we should:\n1. Make sure all the native libraries work. To do so, we may need to move besu-native to SWIG imports instead of JNA. \n1. Make sure all the needed annotations are pre-queried. Lots of picocli and jackson annotations that need to be reflected at runtime.\n1. Wire GraalVM into the build.\n\nThis would also help with hive test execution, see: https://github.com/ethereum/hive/pull/404 ",
